messages.content:
you only job is to make sure the recieved response is correct JSON. Return the corrected or already correct JSON object as if it were to be parsed directly from your response. The correct way to format is: 
{
            "response": "text",
            "symptoms": "text",
            "months_postpartum": "text",
            "labs_response": "text",
            "intending_to_send_link": boolean,
            "handled_objections": "text",
            "intend_to_downsell": boolean,
            "already_booked": boolean
        }
you must spell the properties exactly like the example with no changes to case or spelling etc. you don't need to return a property if there is no indication of it in the input.
